						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/DFID-research-funding-framework-2005-2007" title="DFID research funding framework 2005-2007" alt="link">DFID research funding framework 2005-2007</a></h2>

	
					<p> <i>DFID, 20 September 2004</i>. Key features of DFID's new three-year strategy include increased funding for research on four themes: sustainable agriculture, especially in Africa; killer diseases; where states do not work for the poor; and the impact of climate change on poverty. Alongside successful existing approaches, new initiatives will include improving communication so that research results have a greater impact on poverty, the use of private-public partnerships, building research capacity within developing countries, and increased collaboration with research councils and other UK funders.</p>
							<p><span class="date">23/12/2004</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/DFID-research-funding-framework-2005-2007">Read more...</a>
