						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Biotechnology-roadmap-for-South-Africa-unveiled" title="Biotechnology 'roadmap' for South Africa unveiled" alt="link">Biotechnology 'roadmap' for South Africa unveiled</a></h2>

	
					<p> <i>SciDev.Net, 17 September 2004</i>. South Africa's science and technology minister, Mosibudi Mangena, has launched an ambitious policy for the country's biotechnology development. The document <i>Biotechnology platforms: strategic review and forecast</i> outlines key areas of focus as well as the technologies needed for the plan to succeed. It identifies the main beneficiaries of advances in biotechnology as health services, agriculture, industry, mining and the environment. But implementing this biotechnology 'roadmap' will require significant advances in genomics, transgenics, cell and tissue culture as well as the so-called 'process and product' technologies, such as diagnostic, analytical and manufacturing technologies and bioinformatics.</p>
							<p><span class="date">23/12/2004</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Biotechnology-roadmap-for-South-Africa-unveiled">Read more...</a>
