						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Kenya-in-new-anti-pest-technology" title="Kenya in new anti-pest technology" alt="link">Kenya in new anti-pest technology</a></h2>

	
					<p> <i>The Nation (Nairobi), 16 September 2004</i>. Kenya has become the first country in Africa to adopt new technology that prevents the development of cross-resistance to commercially available pesticides and insecticides. The technology, known as 'ketoenol technology' will help horticultural exporters maintain their lead in the EU market where Kenya commands a 25% share. Oberon, which belongs to a new class of chemicals known as ketoenols, has been developed by Bayer Crop Science Division. The product is effective against both spider mites and whiteflies that are resistant to most other insecticides in which it acts by preventing proper biosynthesis of fatty acids.</p>
							<p><span class="date">23/12/2004</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Kenya-in-new-anti-pest-technology">Read more...</a>
