						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/New-plan-to-rid-Africa-of-obsolete-pesticides" title="New plan to rid Africa of obsolete pesticides" alt="link">New plan to rid Africa of obsolete pesticides</a></h2>

	
					<p> <i>Mail &amp; Guardian, 2 September 2004</i>. A special initiative to rid Africa of vast stockpiles of poisonous, obsolete chemical pesticides posing serious health risks has been launched by the multi-partnered <a href="http://www.africastockpiles.org" target="_blank">African Stockpiles Programme </a>(ASP). The redundant pesticides stored and kept in many African countries contribute to land and water degradation and pose a serious danger to man and beast. The ASP plans to get rid of an estimated 50,000 tons of toxic pesticides and associated waste, as well as tens of thousands of tons of contaminated soil that have accumulated over periods as long as 40 years.</p>
							<p><span class="date">23/12/2004</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/New-plan-to-rid-Africa-of-obsolete-pesticides">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
