						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Announcing-ELDIS-Key-Issue-guides-on-agricultural-biotechnology-and-governance" title="Announcing ELDIS Key Issue guides on agricultural biotechnology and governance" alt="link">Announcing ELDIS Key Issue guides on agricultural biotechnology and governance</a></h2>

	
					<p> <i>ELDIS, 20 August 2004</i>. This new series of guides, developed in collaboration with the Institute of Development Studies, examine the current scientific, legal and governance processes surrounding genetically modified organisms (GMOs) and agriculture. Emerging research suggests that in order to respond better to the concerns of marginalised farmers and consumers, policy and regulatory processes must be 'democratised' to become more responsive and accountable. Key issues include food security, the private sector and intellectual property rights, the influence of trade, regulation and approaches to science policy, developing appropriate technology, citizen rights and participation in the governance of biotechnology.</p>
							<p><span class="date">23/12/2004</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Announcing-ELDIS-Key-Issue-guides-on-agricultural-biotechnology-and-governance">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
